{
  "texts": [
    "The value of the kth resonance at time step t is h t k = sin(2πkϕ t) with ϕ t = ∑ t τ=0 f τ 0, where f τ 0 is the fundamental frequency at time τ.",
    "The spectrogram of h t forms the harmonic excitation in the frequency domain H t (f), and the voice excitation is",
    "Noise excitation.",
    "The noise pathway models consonant sounds (plosives and fricatives).",
    "It is generated by passing a stationary Gaussian white noise excitation through the unvoice filter."
  ]
}